DATA TO RETRIEVE (in this order):

1. SPOT PRICES (live)
   Sources: SMARD (smard.de) for DE, EPEX SPOT where accessible
   Retrieve: Current intraday price (€/MWh), today's day-ahead price curve, 
   yesterday's price at this same hour (for comparison)

2. PRICE FORECAST (next 4–8h)
   Sources: Energy Charts (energy-charts.info) (more important source), SMARD forecast data, 
   Montel News if accessible
   Retrieve: Expected price direction and any forecast values available.
   If sources conflict, report both and note the discrepancy.

3. WEATHER & SOLAR IRRADIANCE (next 4–8h)
   Use these sources in priority order (1 = most trusted for solar irradiance):
     1. Global Solar Atlas (https://globalsolaratlas.info/map) — shortwave radiation, direct & diffuse radiation
     2. Ventusky (ventusky.com) — cloud cover, wind speed
     3. WetterOnline (wetteronline.de) — general forecast cross-check
     4. Windinfo (windinfo.eu) — longer-range cross-check only
   Retrieve per source: cloud cover (%), temperature (°C), wind speed (km/h), 
   shortwave radiation (W/m²), direct radiation, diffuse radiation.
   Compare to: monthly average irradiance for [LOCATION] at this time of year.

4. AGGREGATE RENEWABLE GENERATION (Germany / regional)
   Sources: SMARD (generation by source, live), Energy Charts
   Retrieve: Current solar + wind feed-in (GW), forecast for next 4–8h, 
   share of renewables in current grid mix (%).

5. GRID FREQUENCY (live)
   Source: Netzfrequenz.info (netzfrequenz.info) or Gridradar (gridradar.net)
   Retrieve: Current frequency (Hz), trend over last 30 min (rising/falling/stable).
   Note: <49.95 Hz = scarcity signal, >50.05 Hz = surplus signal.

6. DEMAND PATTERNS (contextual)
   Assess based on: current time of day, day of week, German public holidays.
   Flag if: it is a peak demand window (07–09h, 17–20h), low-demand night/weekend, 
   or a public holiday (demand typically 10–20% lower).

7. RECENT PRICE VOLATILITY
   Source: SMARD intraday price chart (last 24h)
   Retrieve: Price range (min/max) in last 24h, note if current price is 
   in top/bottom 25% of that range.

